T9 236 Anonymous23 : A minimum of 3 satellites are needed for position, but the results are mostly useless to the average person with that few satellites.
T9 237 Anonymous23 : 4 or more are needed.As per Wikipedia:"It might seem three satellites are enough to solve for position, since space has three dimensions.
T9 238 Anonymous23 : However, even a very small clock error multiplied by the very large speed of light19â"the speed at which satellite signals propagateâ"results in a large positional error.
T9 239 Anonymous23 : Therefore receivers use four or more satellites to solve for x, y, z, and t, which is used to correct the receiver's clock.
T9 240 Anonymous23 : While most GPS applications use the computed location only and effectively hide the very accurately computed time, it is used in a few specialized GPS applications such as time transfer, traffic signal timing, and synchronization of cell phone base stations.
T9 241 Anonymous23 : "And to give some credit to this post, as per Ahmed El-Rabbany in "Introduction to GPS:  The Global Positioining System""To determine the receiver's point position at any time, the satellite coordinates as well as a minimum of four ranges to four satellites are required 2.
T9 242 Anonymous23 : The receiver gets the satellite coordinates through the navigation message, while the ranges are obtained from either the C/A-code or the PY-code, depending on the receiver type civilian or military.
T9 243 Anonymous23 : As mentioned before, the measured pseudoranges are contaiminated by both the satellite and receiver clock synchronization errors.
T9 244 Anonymous23 : Correcting the satellite clock errors may be done by applying the satellite clock correction in the navigation message; the receiver clock error is treated as an additional unknown parameter in the estimation process 2.
T9 245 Anonymous23 : This brings the total number of unknown parameters to four; three for the receiver coordinates and one for the receiver clock error.
T9 246 Anonymous23 : This is the reason why at least four satellites are needed.
T9 247 Anonymous23 : "If you've ever turned on your GPS and it has initially said that you were across the country, that's likely because it only resolved 3 satellites.
